Vice President Mike Pence and Senator Tim Scott hosted an African American economic opportunity listening session. The session included small business owners, community leaders, and finance industry leaders. The Vice President highlighted President Trump's commitment to removing barriers to entrepreneurship and economic growth. Key topics discussed were increasing access to capital for small businesses, reducing regulatory burdens from Dodd-Frank, expanding access to education through school choice and vocational education, and allocating more resources to law enforcement. The focus of the discussion was on empowering and revitalizing distressed communities through economic development to improve the quality of life for all Americans, including African Americans.